[[File:God of Saikei.png|thumb|right|170px|Saikei Shin]] '''Saikei Shin''' (歳刑神, さいぎょうしん) is one of the {{ill|Eight Guardian Deities|ja|八将神|1=Eight Directional Deities|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Eight Guardian Deities|13=User:Immanuelle/Eight Directional Deities|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Eight Guardian Deities|13=User:Immanuelle/Eight Directional Deities|qq=}} in [[:en:Onmyōdō|Onmyōdō]]. In some calendar texts, it may also be written as "さいけい" or "さいぎょう" (Saikei or Saigyō). In [[:en:Buddhism|Buddhism]], the {{ill|honji|ja|本地仏|1=Honji_suijaku#Honji Buddha|lt=Honji Buddha|2=ja|3=本地垂迹|4=fr|5=Honji suijaku|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/honji|13=User:Immanuelle/Honji_suijaku#Honji Buddha|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/honji|13=User:Immanuelle/Honji_suijaku#Honji Buddha|qq=}} of Saikei Shin is {{ill|Kenrochijin|ja|堅牢地神|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kenrochijin|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kenrochijin|qq=}}.
